article.description: Barksdale scores 18, leads IUPUI past IPFW, 63-58
article.headline: Barksdale scores 18, leads IUPUI past IPFW, 63-58
article.linkText: Barksdale scores 18, leads IUPUI past IPFW, 63-58
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Marcellus Barksdale scored five of 18 points in the final 34 seconds to help IUPUI hold off IPFW for a 63-58 win on Sunday night. A dunk by D.J. McCall gave IUPUI (5-10, 1-0 Summit League) a 43-29 lead with 15:29 left, but a 3-pointer by Joe Edwards sparked a 15-2 run -- including eight points by Michael Calder -- which cut the IPFW deficit to 45-44 with 9:15 to go. Barksdale hit a pair of free throws to make it 56-48 with 3:38 remaining, but IUPUI went scoreless over the next 3-plus minutes and the Mastodons trailed by two, 56-54, with less than a minute to play. After Barksdale broke the Jaguars drought with a three-point play, Max Landis answered with a 3 to make it 59-57 with 25 seconds left. DavRon Williams and Barksdale made two free throws apiece from there to seal it. Edwards scored a season-high 17 for IPFW (7-8, 0-2), which has lost six-straight games against Div. I opponents.
